Process for making png images of group names for subgroup diagrams:

 - run dump-group-names.py  It produces eqguts.tex which has the latex and
   prettyindex to be uploaded to the db

 - move eqguts.tex to the images directory

 - in the images directory run latex eq.tex

 - in the images directory run dvipng -D 120 -bg Transparent eq.dvi
   (the images currently in gps_images were rendered at 120 dpi; dvipng's
   default of 100 dpi produces images that are ~17% smaller)

 - run load-img.py from this directory

Incremental process (only render names missing from gps_images, e.g. after
new groups/subgroups are added; see https://github.com/LMFDB/lmfdb/issues/7028):

 - run dump-missing-group-names.py instead of dump-group-names.py (writes
   eqguts.tex/prettyindex containing only the missing names, most-referenced
   first)

 - move eqguts.tex to the images directory, then run latex and dvipng there
   as above

 - run load-new-imgs.py from this directory: it writes "imageadder" with only
   the genuinely new rows and appends them with db.gps_images.copy_from,
   instead of rewriting the whole table

Macro consistency (images/eq.tex vs the website's KaTeX macros):

 - group tex names are rendered both by KaTeX on the website (macro list in
   lmfdb/templates/base.html) and by latex here (preamble in images/eq.tex).
   Every group-name macro in base.html must also be defined in eq.tex,
   otherwise dump-missing-group-names.py would misclassify names using it as
   broken and silently skip them (they keep showing up as '?' in diagrams).

 - macro_check.py compares the two macro sets (names only; a few bodies
   differ on purpose, matching the images already in gps_images) and knows
   the short list of base.html macros that are deliberately image-irrelevant
   (\Aut, \Gal, number sets, ...).  It runs automatically at the start of
   dump-missing-group-names.py and can be run standalone:
   sage -python macro_check.py

 - when adding a group-name macro to base.html, add it to images/eq.tex in
   the same change; macro_check.py will refuse to dump until you do.
